{"title_page": "Barguzin (rural locality)", "text_new": "{{Other uses|Barguzin (disambiguation){{!}}Barguzin}}\n\n{{Infobox Russian rural locality\n|en_name=Barguzin\n|ru_name=\u0411\u0430\u0440\u0433\u0443\u0437\u0438\u043d\n|loc_name1=\n|loc_lang1=\n|image_skyline=\n|image_caption=\n|coordinates = {{coord|53|37|N|109|38|E|display=inline,title}}\n|map_label_position=bottom\n|image_coa=\n|coa_caption=\n|image_flag=\n|flag_caption=\n|anthem=\n|anthem_ref=\n|holiday=\n|holiday_ref=\n|federal_subject=[[Republic of Buryatia]]\n|federal_subject_ref=<ref name=\"2010Census\" />\n|adm_data_as_of=2010\n|adm_district_jur=[[Barguzinsky District]]\n|adm_district_jur_ref=<ref name=\"2010Census\" />\n|adm_ctr_of=Barguzinsky District\n|adm_ctr_of_ref=<ref name=\"2010Census\" />\n|inhabloc_cat=Rural locality\n|inhabloc_cat_ref=<ref name=\"2010Census\" />\n|inhabloc_type=''[[Village#Russia|Selo]]''\n|inhabloc_type_ref=<ref name=\"2010Census\" />\n|mun_data_as_of=\n|mun_district_jur=\n|mun_district_jur_ref=\n|rural_settlement_jur=\n|rural_settlement_jur_ref=\n|mun_admctr_of=\n|mun_admctr_of_ref=\n|leader_title=\n|leader_title_ref=\n|leader_name=\n|leader_name_ref=\n|representative_body=\n|representative_body_ref=\n|area_of_what=\n|area_as_of=\n|area_km2=\n|area_km2_ref=\n|pop_2010census=5702\n|pop_2010census_ref=<ref name=\"2010Census\">{{ru-pop-ref|2010Census}}</ref>\n|pop_density=\n|pop_density_as_of=\n|pop_density_ref=\n|pop_latest=\n|pop_latest_date=\n|pop_latest_ref=\n|established_date=\n|established_title=\n|established_date_ref=\n|current_cat_date=\n|current_cat_date_ref=\n|prev_name1=\n|prev_name1_date=\n|prev_name1_ref=\n|postal_codes=\n|postal_codes_ref=\n|dialing_codes=\n|dialing_codes_ref=\n|website=\n|website_ref=\n|commonscat=\n|date=March 2013\n}}\n'''Barguzin''' ({{lang-ru|\u0411\u0430\u0440\u0433\u0443\u0437\u0438\u043d}}, {{lang-bua|\u0411\u0430\u0440\u0433\u0430\u0436\u0430\u043d}}, ''Bargajan'') is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a ''[[village#Russia|selo]]'') and the [[administrative center]] of [[Barguzinsky District]] in the [[Republic of Buryatia]], [[Russia]], located on the left bank of the [[Barguzin River]] at the southern end of the [[Barguzin Valley]]. Barguzin lies at an elevation of {{convert|491|m|sp=us}} and is {{convert|240|km|sp=us}} from [[Ulan-Ude]]. Population: {{ru-census|p2010=5,702|p2002=6,164|p1989=6,151}}\n\n==Transportation==\nThe P438 road leads southwest to the ''selo'' of [[Adamovo, Republic of Buryatia|Adamovo]], the urban-type settlement of [[Ust-Barguzin]], and eventually to [[Ulan-Ude]]; it leads northeast along the Barguzin Valley to [[Ulyun (rural locality)|Ulyun]] and [[Kurumkan]].\n\nBarguzin is served by the [[Barguzin Airport]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Barguzin Airport|url=http://www.ourairports.com/airports/RU-0105/|publisher=OurAirports|accessdate=January 24, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Climate==\nBarguzin has a [[subarctic climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]] ''Dwc''), with severely cold winters and warm summers. [[Precipitation (meteorology)|Precipitation]] is quite low but is significantly higher in July and August than at other times of the year.\n\n<div style=\"width:70%;\">\n{{Weather box\n|location=Barguzin\n|metric first=yes\n|single line=yes\n|Jan record high C=2.3\n|Feb record high C=5.6\n|Mar record high C=13.4\n|Apr record high C=24.5\n|May record high C=34.6\n|Jun record high C=35.2\n|Jul record high C = 36.8\n|Aug record high C = 36.8\n|Sep record high C = 27.7\n|Oct record high C = 20.5\n|Nov record high C = 13.8\n|Dec record high C = 5.0\n|Jan high C = -22.4\n|Feb high C = -16.8\n|Mar high C = -4.5\n|Apr high C = 6.1\n|May high C = 15.3\n|Jun high C = 22.9\n|Jul high C = 25.2\n|Aug high C = 22.2\n|Sep high C = 14.7\n|Oct high C = 4.9\n|Nov high C = -7.6\n|Dec high C = -17.3\n|Jan mean C = -27.3\n|Feb mean C = -23.2\n|Mar mean C = -11.7\n|Apr mean C = 0.0\n|May mean C = 8.3\n|Jun mean C = 15.5\n|Jul mean C = 18.6\n|Aug mean C = 16.0\n|Sep me